obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6708)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6708&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Governors`
  line `(Emoluments, Allowances and Privileges) Act, 1982.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India ^1***.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^2 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 34 of 2019, s. 95 and the Fifth Schedule`
  line `(w.e.f. 31-10- 2019).`
  line
  line `2 1st April 1987, vide notification No. G.S.R. 342(E), dated 30th March, 1987, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II, sec.`
  line `3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6709)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6709&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "ex-Governor" means a person who has been the Governor of a State or two or more States;`
  line
  line `(aa) "Governor" means the Governor, or any person discharging the functions of the Governor, of`
  line `any State or of two or more States;]`
  line
  line `(b) "maintenance",--`
  line
  line `(i) in relation to official residences, includes the provision of electricity, gas and water;`
  line
  line `(ii) in relation to motor vehicles, includes the pay and allowances of chauffeurs and the`
  line `provision of oil and petrol or other fuel;`
  line
  line `(c) "members of the family", in relation to a Governor, means the ^2[spouse, dependent children`
  line `and the dependent parents] of the Governor;`
  line
  line `(d) "official residences", in relation to a Governor, means such residences as may be specified by`
  line `the President, by notification in the Official Gazette, as the official residences of the Governor and includes the staff quarters and other buildings appurtenant thereto and the gardens thereof;`
  line
  line `(e) "rules" means rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "State" does not include a Union territory.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 8 of 2014, s. 2, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 1 of 2009, s. 2, for "spouse and the dependent children" (w.e.f. 1-1-2007).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6710)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title Emoluments.
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6710&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `There shall be paid to every Governor emoluments at the rate of ^1[rupees ^2[three`
  line `lakh fifty thousand] permensem]:`
  line
  line `Provided that if a Governor, at the time of his appointment,--`
  line
  line `(a) is in receipt of a pension (other than disability or wound pension) in respect of any previous`
  line `service under the Government of India or any of its predecessor Governments or under the`
  line `Government of a State or any of its predecessor Governments his emoluments shall be reduced,--`
  line
  line `(i) by the amount of that pension; and`
  line
  line `(ii) if he has, before such appointment, received in lieu of a portion of the pension due to him`
  line `in respect of such previous service, the commuted value thereof, by the amount of that portion of`
  line `the pension;^3[or]`
  line
  line `^4* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) is in receipt of any benefit by way of contributory provident fund, his emoluments shall be`
  line `reduced by the pension equivalent of such benefit.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "rupees thirty-six thousand per mensem" (w.e.f.1-1-2006).`
  line
  line `2 Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s 161, for "one lakh ten thousand" (w.e.f 1-1-2016).`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by Act 1 of 1994, s. 2, for "and" (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
  line
  line `4. Sub-clause (iii) omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-6-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6711)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Leave allowance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6711&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to any rules made in this behalf, the President shall grant such`
  line `leave to a Governor as he may consider necessary.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a Governor is granted leave by the President, he shall, during the period of such leave, be`
  line `paid leave allowance at such rate as the President may by order determine:`
  line
  line `Provided that such leave allowance shall be reduced to the extent, if any, to which the emoluments of`
  line `the Governor are liable to be reduced under the proviso to section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6712)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Use and maintenance of official residences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6712&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `A Governor shall be entitled, without payment of`
  line `rent, to the use of his official residences throughout his term of office and no charge shall fall on the`
  line `Governor personally in respect of the furnishing or the maintenance of such residences.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6713)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Household establishment.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6713&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf, no charge shall fall on a`
  line `Governor personally in respect of pay, allowances or pension or other emoluments paid to, or facilities`
  line `provided for, the members of the household establishment provided to the Governor.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6723)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Medical treatment`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6723&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this behalf, a Governor and the members of his`
  line `family shall be entitled during the term of his office and thereafter also, to free medical attendance,`
  line `accommodation and treatment in the hospitals maintained by the Central Government or the Government`
  line `of any State.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6724)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title Conveyance
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6724&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) A Governor shall be entitled to use without payment of rent or hire, such`
  line `number of motor vehicles as the President may by order determine.`
  line
  line `(2) No charge shall fall on a Governor personally in respect of the maintenance of the motor vehicles`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1).`
  line
  line `(3) The use of the motor vehicles referred to in sub-section (1) by the members of the family of a`
  line `Governor shall be regulated by rules made in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6725)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Traveling allowance on assumption or vacation of office`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6725&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf, a Governor shall be entitled to traveling allowance for himself and the members of his family and`
  line `for the transport of his and his family's effects--`
  line
  line `(a) in respect of the journey for assuming office from the place where he is ordinarily residing to`
  line `the place of his duty; and`
  line
  line `(b) in respect of the journey on relinquishing office from the place of his duty to the place where`
  line `he would ordinarily reside thereafter or if he is to take up any other office under the Government`
  line `(including the office of the Governor of another State) after such relinquishment, to the place of duty`
  line `with respect to such other office.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6726)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Allowances for renewing furnishings and for maintenance of official residences.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6726&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `Subject to`
  line `any rules made in this behalf, a Governor shall be entitled to such allowances for renewing the furnishings`
  line `and for the maintenance of the official residences, as the President may by order determine.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6727)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Other privileges and allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6727&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of enabling a Governor to discharge`
  line `conveniently and with dignity the duties of his office, he shall be—`
  line
  line `(i) entitled to such other privileges as may be prescribed by rules made in this behalf, and`
  line
  line `(ii) paid, subject to any rules made in this behalf, such amount, as the President may, by general`
  line `or special order, determine by way of the following, namely:—`
  line
  line `(a) entertainment allowance;`
  line
  line `(b) hospitality grant;`
  line
  line `(c) household establishment expenses;`
  line
  line `(d) office expenses;`
  line
  line `(e) contract allowance, i.e., an allowance for miscellaneous expenses;`
  line
  line `(f) tour expenses; and`
  line
  line `(g) such other allowances or expenses as may be provided for by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6728)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Additional expenses`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6728&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where, in the case of any Governor, the President is satisfied that the`
  line `amount authorised under this Act by way of any allowances or for meeting any expenses with respect to`
  line `any matter requires to be increased or that a need has arisen to sanction expenses with respect to any`
  line `matter for which provision, though permissible, has not been made in the rules made under this Act, he`
  line `may by special order increase such amount or sanction such expenses to such extent as may be specified`
  line `in such order.`
  line
  line `(2) An order may be made under sub-section (1) so as to have retrospective effect.`
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12_a:
  sectionId (6729)
  sectionNo 12A
  orderNo 13
  title `Entitlement of ex-Governor to secretarial assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 8 of 2014, s. 3 (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6729&sectionno=12A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_12_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[12A. Entitlement of ex-Governor to secretarial assistance. Subject to any rules made in this`
  line `behalf, the ex-Governor shall, for the remainder of his life, be entitled to secretarial assistance of one`
  line `Personal Assistant on reimbursement basis:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such ex-Governor is re-appointed to the office of the Governor or elected to`
  line `Parliament or the State Legislature or appointed to any office of profit under the Union or a State`
  line `Government, he shall not be entitled for such secretarial assistance for the period during which he holds`
  line `such office.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6730)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 8 of 2014, s. 4 (w.e.f. 4-3-2014).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6730&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The President may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules`
  line `for the purpose of giving effect to the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) grant of leave to a Governor under Section 4;`
  line
  line `(b) matters relating to the household establishment provided to a Governor under section 6;`
  line
  line `(c) medical attendance, accommodation and treatment of a Governor and the members of his`
  line `family under section 7;`
  line
  line `(d) the use of motor vehicles by the members of the family of a Governor under sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 8;`
  line
  line `(e) the travelling allowance on assumption or vacation of office of a Governor under section 9;`
  line
  line `(f) allowance for renewing the furnishings and for the maintenance of the official residences`
  line `under section 10;`
  line
  line `(g) the privileges to which a Governor is entitled and the allowances or expenses payable to a`
  line `Governor under section 11;`
  line
  line `^1[(h) the manner of providing secretarial assistance and reimbursement under section 12A.]`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the President under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days, which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6731)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title Validation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6731&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) Every special order issued, before the commencement of this Act, by the`
  line `President in regard to the allowances, expenses (including medical expenses) or privileges of any`
  line `Governor (other than the Governor of Nagaland) shall, notwithstanding that such order was made with`
  line `retrospective effect, or is inconsistent with any general order issued under any law with respect to those`
  line `matters, be as valid and effective as if such special order formed part of this sub-section and this subsection`
  line `had been in force at all material times.`
  line
  line `(2) Every general or special order issued, before the commencement of this Act, by the President in`
  line `regard to the allowances, expenses (including medical expenses) or privileges of the Governor of`
  line `Nagaland shall, notwithstanding that such order was made with retrospective effect, be as valid and`
  line `effective as if it formed part of this sub-section and this sub-section had been in force at all material times.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6732)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title Saving.
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622&sectionId=6732&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00008_198243_1517807326622
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act or the rules made thereunder shall have effect so as to`
  line `diminish the emoluments and allowances of any Governor during his term of office.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
obj_root_law_translations_hi:
  title `राज्यपाल (उपलब्धिऔयां, भत्ते और विशेषाधिकार) अधिनियम, 1982`
  sourceUrl `https://www.indiacode.nic.in/bitstream/123456789/1838/2/H1982-43.pdf`
  sourceKind pdf
  fetchedAt `2026-05-10T10:18:31.363Z`
